  Imagine Home  |
  Science
         Explore a universe of black holes, dark matter, and quasars... A
         universe full of extremely high energies, high densities, high
         pressures, and extremely intense magnetic fields which allow us to test
         our understanding of the laws of physics.
         For more advanced articles, try the Advanced Science page

                                 The Basics
    Start your exploration of the high energy universe here. This section
    includes explanations of some of the concepts and principles used to
                     study and understand the universe.
   The Electromagnetic Spectrum
   Multiwavelength Astronomy X-ray Astronomy
   Lightcurves, Spectra, and Images
                             Gamma-Ray Astronomy

                               Cosmic Objects
    The universe is more than just stars, dust, and empty space. Explore
     some of the objects that make up our universe, from our own sun to
                      distant pulsars and black holes.
